The paper deals with inferring information flow in neuronal circuits, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.NE). The paper also discusses information-theoretic concepts such as transfer entropy and directed information, which are relevant to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches upon the subject of automated methods for inferring causality, which is relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of understanding fundamental logic processes in cognitive processing, which is relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
